CENSUS AND STATISTICS.

Mr. FISHER moved second reading of Bill (No. 163') to amend the Census and Statistics Act. He said: This is simply an Act to substitute the names of the new pro- vinces for the name of the Northwest Ter- ritories in the Census and Statistics Act, which were passed in the early part of this session.
